Vestiture. Base of scape with 2–3 long bristles, the longest 2.3 x as long as the scape diameter, bristles shorter ( 0.5 x scape diameter) and finer to the apex of scape; pedicel bristles slightly longer than diameter of fl. 3 ; on posterior surface of fl. 1 two very long bristles, ca. 3.7 x diameter of fl. 3 (
Fig. 8
), and from fl. 2 forward, a sequence of erect bristles progressively shorter, aligned (
Fig. 9
), one or two on each flagellomere, as long as 2.2 x fl. 3 diameter on fl.2, 2x on fl.3, 1x on fl. 4 , 0.5 x on fl. 5 . The remaining pilosity as described for the genus.

Geographical distribution. Apparently endemic to the southwestern Amazon, Amazonas, Rondônia, Acre, Mato Grosso, Brazil (
Fig. 16
).
